comment: Correctly called OOB last touched by Faried (DEN). Memphis is awarded possession.
Harris (DEN) makes incidental contact with Chalmers (MEM) prior to the ball going OOB that does not affect his RSBQ.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was conclusive video evidence that showed that the ball was last touched by Chalmers (MEM) prior to going OOB. The ruling on the court was overturned and Denver was awarded possession.
Faried (DEN) sets the screen on Hairston (MEM) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Conley (MEM) pushes Mudiay (DEN) with his right hand and the contact affects Mudiay's drive to the basket.
Barnes (MEM) makes contact with Mudiay (DEN) that affects his RSBQ and causes him to lose control of the ball.
Faried (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Randolph's (MEM) shot attempt.
Arthur (DEN) commits a take foul on Barnes (MEM).
Mudiay (DEN) commits a take foul on Chalmers (MEM).
Jokic (DEN) extends his arms as he sets the screen on Hairston (MEM) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Randolph (MEM) makes incidental contact with Jokic (DEN) that does not affect his FOM away from the ball.
Randolph (MEM) makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm that affects his shot attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined that the foul committed by Harris (DEN) met the criteria for a Flagrant Foul 1. All Flagrant Fouls are reviewed by the League Office.
